result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason L. Baur was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case Called: 1:16 p.m.
Clerk: Nicole.   
INCLUDES: 15CF1228, 16CF1058.
State appears by ADA Kerri Puig. 
Defendant appears in person from MCJ with Atty Jerod Barkley.

Plea Quest/Waiver of Rights filed. VRCW.

PLEA: 
15CF1228
Count 1 (Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money)>>GUILTY.

16CF1058
Count 1 (Forgery-Writings or Objects - Repeater)>>GUILTY.
Count 2 (Forgery-Writings or Objects - Repeater)>>GUILTY.

C.L. makes statement.

COURT advises defendant of rights (including constitutional rights) & penalties & questions defendant to understanding; 
COURT finds plea & waiver of rights freely & vol made, a factual basis & defendant guilty;

COURT ORDERS:
15CF1228
Count 1 (Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money)>>
SWH for 5 years probation; CONDITIONS: 1 year MCJ w/ no objection to EMP; Assessments/Treatment/Counseling deemed appropriate by agent; Maintain FTW/School or combination of the two, and if not so fully engaged, complete 9 hours CS per week; Maintain absolute sobriety from drugs and alcohol and no possession of controlled substances unless taken in the amount prescribed; AODA and follow through; No contact with A.O. and L.S.; write apology letters to A.O. and L.S.; pay restitution in the amount of $1,110.00 to L.S.; pay CC/DNA surcharge and provide sample. 

16CF1058
Count 1 (Forgery-Writings or Objects - Repeater)>>
SWH for 5 years probation; CONDITIONS: Assessments/Treatment/Counseling deemed appropriate by agent; Maintain FTW/School or combination of the two, and if not so fully engaged, complete 9 hours CS per week; Maintain absolute sobriety from drugs and alcohol and no possession of controlled substances unless taken in the amount prescribed; AODA and follow through; No contact with A.O. and L.S.; write apology letters to A.O. and L.S; pay CC/DNA surcharge and provide sample. 

Count 2 (Forgery-Writings or Objects - Repeater)>>
SWH for 5 years probation; CONDITIONS: Assessments/Treatment/Counseling deemed appropriate by agent; Maintain FTW/School or combination of the two, and if not so fully engaged, complete 9 hours CS per week; Maintain absolute sobriety from drugs and alcohol and no possession of controlled substances unless taken in the amount prescribed; AODA and follow through; No contact with A.O. and L.S.; write apology letters to A.O. and L.S.; pay restitution in the amount of $50,968.00 to A.O.; pay CC/DNA surcharge and provide sample.

COURT grants 67 days jail credit to be applied to each case.
COURT orders payment of no less than $75.00 per month regarding restitution.
COURT has no objection to transfer of probation to Langlade County.
